ow%20highly%20questionable%2C%20it%20seems%20that%20the%20UK%20must%20look%20for%20alternative%20approaches.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20least%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabcnews.go.com%2FPolitics%2Fhouthis-shoot-growing-number-us-drones%2Fstory%3Fid%3D121099082%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E15%20Reapers%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20have%20been%20shot%20down%20by%20Houthi%20rebels%20over%20Yemen%20since%20October%202023%2C%20with%20seven%20destroyed%20in%20March%20and%20April%202025%2C%20estimated%20losses%20at%20or%20above%20%24500%20million.%20The%20threat%20to%20the%20Reapers%20would%20likely%20be%20much%20greater%20against%20a%20more%20advanced%20military%2C%20which%20fields%20larger%20and%20more%20accurate%20air%20defenses.%20Houthi%20air%20defenses%20are%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.janes.com%2Fosint-insights%2Fdefence-news%2Fyemeni-rebels-unveil-new-sam%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efar%20from%20cutting%20edge%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%20old%20Soviet-made%20SA-2%20and%20SA-6%20missiles%20date%20back%20to%20the%201960s%2C%20or%20are%20Iranian%20weapons%20based%20on%20those%20designs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20Ukraine's%20Turkish-made%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fturkeys-bayraktar-tb2-drones-ineffective-ukraine-war-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ETB2%20Bayraktar%20drones%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%94%20armed%20with%20laser-guided%20anti-tank%20missiles%20%E2%80%94%20initially%20devastated%20Russian%20armored%20columns%20that%20invaded%20in%20February%202022.%20But%20dozens%20of%20TB2s%20were%20destroyed%20once%20Russian%20air%20defenses%20were%20deployed%2C%20and%20the%20Bayraktar%20has%20disappeared%20from%20Ukrainian%20skies.%20Meanwhile%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jpost.com%2Farab-israeli-conflict%2Fhezbollahs-painful-blow-israeli-uav-struck-down-in-lebanon-795950%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIsrael's%20Hermes%20drones%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20have%20fallen%20victim%20to%20Hezbollah%20anti-aircraft%20missiles.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20has%20left%20Britain%20in%20a%20quandary.%20The%20British%20Army's%20MALE%20drone%2C%20the%20Watchkeeper%2C%20has%20proven%20a%20failure.%20Based%20on%20Israel's%20Hermes%20450%2C%20the%20Watchkeeper%20produced%20by%20Thales%20Group%20and%20Elbit%20Systems%20first%20flew%20in%202010%2C%20but%20wasn't%20deployed%20until%202018.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.flightglobal.com%2Fdefence%2Fwhy-uks-watchkeeper-uav-failed-the-test-of-time%2F160918.article%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EDelays%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20technical%20issues%20and%20several%20crashes%20spurred%20the%20retirement%20of%20the%20Watchkeeper%20fleet%20in%20March%2C%20less%20than%20seven%20years%20after%20it%20was%20fielded.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20UK's%20military%20says%20the%20medium-altitude%20WatchKeeper%20drone%20is%20already%20obsolete.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68261c0d68a2929008016d3b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22716%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20UK's%20military%20says%20the%20medium-altitude%20WatchKeeper%20drone%20is%20already%20obsolete.%3Cp%3ECpl%20Matthews%2FUK%20MOD%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20getting%20rid%20of%20Watchkeeper%20because%20that%20system%20has%20been%20in%20service%20since%202010%20and%2C%20according%20to%20all%20the%20military%20chiefs%2C%20is%20out%20of%20date%2C%26quot%3B%20Lord%20Vernon%20Croaker%2C%20a%20senior%20official%20in%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%2C%20told%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%20in%20November%202024.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20a%20range%20of%20almost%20100%20miles%2C%20the%20Watchkeeper%20could%20peer%20deep%20into%20enemy%20areas%20and%20locate%20supply%20depots%2C%20airbases%20and%20other%20targets%20for%20long-range%20artillery%2C%20missiles%20and%20aircraft.%20Thus%20the%20British%20Army%20is%20now%20embarked%20on%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fukdefencejournal.org.uk%2Farmy-kicks-off-project-to-replace-watchkeeper-drones%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EProject%20Corvus%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20calls%20for%20a%20long-endurance%20surveillance%20drone%20that%20can%20stay%20airborne%20for%2024%20hours%20and%20fly%20deep%20penetration%20missions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20this%20may%20only%20result%20in%20another%20MALE%20drone%20too%20expensive%20to%20buy%20in%20quantity%2C%20and%20too%20vulnerable%20to%20be%20expendable.%20These%20same%20issues%20threaten%20the%20Reaper%20(%2430%20million)%20and%20the%20Bayraktar%20TB-2%20(%245%20million).%20%26quot%3BAssessments%20in%20Ukraine%20would%20suggest%20that%20the%20point%20at%20which%20a%20UAV%20becomes%20attritable%20is%20a%20unit%20price%20below%20%24200%2C000%20for%20ISR%20%5Bsurveillance%20missions%5D%2C%26quot%3B%20Tollast%20wrote.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20creates%20a%20cost-benefit%20dilemma.%20Hordes%20of%20cheap%2C%20expendable%20first-person%20view%20(FPV)%20drones%20have%20become%20the%20dominant%20weapon%20in%20the%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20paralyzing%20bold%20battlefield%20maneuvers%20and%20practically%20driving%20armored%20vehicles%20off%20the%20battlefield.%20These%20are%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-drone-defense-tech-industry-warfare-russia-attacks-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emass-produced%20commercial%20drones%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20can%20be%20rigged%20for%20military%20missions%20at%20a%20total%20cost%20of%20hundreds%20of%20dollars.%20Most%20of%20these%20have%20limited%20payload%20capacity%2C%20altitude%20and%20a%20range%20of%20only%20around%2010%20miles.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20the%20other%20end%20of%20the%20spectrum%20is%20the%20airliner-sized%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbreakingdefense.com%2F2022%2F07%2Fexclusive-air-forces-rq-4-global-hawk-drones-headed-for-the-boneyard-in-fy27%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ERQ-4%20Global%20Hawk%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20a%20high-altitude%20%24200%20million%20drone%20that%20is%20being%20retired%20from%20the%20US%20military.%20A%20Global%20Hawk%20was%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Firan-shot-down-one-of-us-militarys-most-advanced-drones-2019-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edestroyed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20an%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defense.gov%2FNews%2FNews-Stories%2Farticle%2Farticle%2F1882497%2Firan-shoots-down-us-global-hawk-operating-in-international-airspace%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIranian%20anti-aircraft%20missile%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%202019.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20middle%20are%20the%20drones%20like%20the%20Reaper%2C%20which%20can%20carry%20a%202-ton%20payload%20of%20missiles%20and%20sensors%2C%20has%20a%20range%20of%201%2C200%20miles%2C%20and%20can%20fly%20at%2050%2C000%20feet.%20The%20Reapers%20were%20essential%20aircraft%20in%20the%20wars%20in%20Iraq%20and%20Afghanistan%20as%20they%20could%20stay%20in%20the%20air%20hunting%20for%20targets%20far%20longer%20than%20a%20crewed%20aircraft%2C%20and%20be%20placed%20in%20more%20dangerous%20airspace%20because%20there%20was%20no%20risk%20to%20a%20human%20flier.%20For%20example%2C%20from%20September%202007%20to%20July%202008%2C%20MQ-9%20flew%20480%20sorties%20totaling%20more%20than%203%2C800%20hours%20in%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20many%20ways%2C%20these%20UAVs%20resemble%20the%20earliest%20drones%2C%20which%20were%20just%20modified%20versions%20of%20manned%20aircraft.%20For%20example%2C%20World%20War%20II%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thisdayinaviation.com%2Ftag%2Fgrumman-f6f-5k-hellcat%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EF6F%20Hellcat%20fighters%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20converted%20into%20remote-controlled%20machines%20for%20target%20practice.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpimaair.org%2Fmuseum-aircraft%2Fteledyne-ryan-aqm-34l-firebee%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAQM-34L%20Firebee%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20flew%20reconnaissance%20missions%20over%20Vietnam%20was%2029%20feet%20long%2C%20not%20much%20shorter%20than%20an%20MQ-9.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20face%20a%20glaring%20problem%3A%20more%20adversaries%20are%20armed%20with%20air%20defense%20missiles%20capable%20of%20knocking%20out%20aircraft-sized%20drones.%20Drones%20like%20the%20MQ-9%20were%20not%20designed%20to%20fly%20in%20areas%20covered%20by%20an%20enemy's%20surface-to-air%20missiles.%20A%20Bayraktar's%20cruise%20speed%20is%20only%2080%20miles%20per%20hour%2C%20while%20even%20a%20relatively%20speedy%20Reaper%20has%20a%20cruise%20speed%20of%20around%20200%20miles%20per%20hour.%20Thus%20even%20a%20militant%20group%20like%20the%20Houthis%20can%20down%20an%20MQ-9%20with%20an%20old%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.centcom.mil%2FMEDIA%2FSTATEMENTS%2FStatements-View%2FArticle%2F1877252%2Fstatement-from-us-central-command-on-attacks-against-us-observation-aircraft%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESoviet%20SA-6%20surface-to-air%20missile%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20puts%20drones%20at%20a%20fork%20in%20the%20road%20%E2%80%94%20go%20low-cost%20and%20large%20volume%20or%20even%20higher-cost%20with%20fewer%20aircraft%20but%20more%20capability.%20America's%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.slashgear.com%2F1653644%2Freaper-drone-replacement-details-mq-next%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EReaper%20replacement%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20may%20do%20the%20latter%3A%20a%20more%20sophisticated%20%E2%80%94%20and%20expensive%20%E2%80%94%20drone%20that%20includes%20stealth%20capabilities%20to%20evade%20radar%3B%20radar%20remains%20the%20primary%20means%20for%20air%20defenses%20to%20detect%20targets.%20For%20Britain%2C%20with%20its%20far%20smaller%20defense%20budget%20of%20roughly%20%2470%20billion%2C%20an%20improved%20MALE%20drone%20isn't%20viable.%20Tollast%20sees%20several%20non-drone%20options%2C%20including%20Low%20Earth%20Orbit%20satellites%2C%20high-altitude%20balloons%2C%20and%20tethered%20aerostats%20(such%20as%20blimps)%2C%20which%20avoid%20the%20vulnerability%20of%20medium-altitude%20drones.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%20satellites%20and%20balloons%20may%20not%20be%20in%20position%20when%20you%20need%20them%2C%20and%20aerostats%20can't%20be%20dispatched%20quickly%20into%20remote%20areas.%20Unless%20a%20technological%20breakthrough%20enables%20small%20UAVs%20to%20enjoy%20the%20capabilities%20of%20their%20larger%20brethren%2C%20the%20inability%20of%20large%20drones%20to%20function%20reduces%20the%20huge%20advantage%20of%20sensing%20the%20battlefield%20that%20the%20US%20and%20Western%20militaries%20have%20enjoyed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EMichael%20Peck%20is%20a%20defense%20writer%20whose%20work%20has%20appeared%20in%20Forbes%2C%20Defense%20News%2C%20Foreign%20Policy%20magazine%2C%20and%20other%20publications.%20He%20holds%20an%20MA%20in%20political%20science%20from%20Rutgers%20Univ.%20Follow%20him%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twitter.com%2F%40mipeck1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3ETwitter%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3C