0would%20present%20much%20of%20a%20challenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20earlier%20in%20her%20career%2C%20Schive%20darted%20around%20dozens%20of%20countries%20as%20a%20clandestine%20service%20officer%20for%20the%20CIA%2C%20focusing%20on%20limiting%20the%20spread%20of%20weapons%20of%20mass%20destruction.%20She%20later%20served%20as%20a%20director%20of%20global%20risk%20consulting%20at%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmckinsey-bcg-and-deloitte-competition-small-boutique-specialized-ai-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBig%20Four%20firm%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENonetheless%2C%20finding%20people%20to%20bake%20the%20European-style%20viennoiserie%20and%20sourdough%20breads%20she'd%20grown%20to%20love%20living%20abroad%20wasn't%20easy%2C%20Schive%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarder%20yet%20was%20getting%20them%20to%20stay%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHiring%20in%20the%20restaurant%20business%20has%20rarely%20been%20straightforward.%20Now%2C%20to%20attract%20and%20retain%20staffers%2C%20some%20employers%20say%20it's%20necessary%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eto%20take%20a%20kitchen-sink%20approach%3A%20deploying%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fidaho-restaurant-kin-employee-wellbeing-workplace-culture-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evarious%20benefits%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20training%2C%20technology%2C%20and%20added%20flexibility%20in%20scheduling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20all-of-the-above%20strategy%20is%20often%20necessary%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fneurodivergent-workers-employers-fill-jobs-unemployment-skills-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elabor%20shortages%3C%2Fa%3E%20remain%20a%20perennial%20challenge%20in%20the%20restaurant%20and%20food%20service%20industry%2C%20which%20is%20estimated%20to%20employ%20about%20one%20in%2010%20US%20workers.%20The%20National%20Restaurant%20Association%20projects%20that%20the%20industry%20will%20add%20200%2C000%20jobs%20in%20the%20US%20in%202025%2C%20boosting%20employment%20to%2015.9%20million%20by%20year-end.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20so-called%20quick-service%20restaurants%2C%20many%20workers%20don't%20last%20a%20year%20or%20even%20six%20months%2C%20David%20Henkes%2C%20a%20senior%20principal%20at%20the%20market%20research%20firm%20Technomic%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20talk%20to%20restaurants%20about%20what%20they're%20doing%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20it%20just%20involves%20trying%20to%20stem%20the%20flow%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20succession%20of%20hires%20and%20quits.%20That's%20because%20people%20often%20view%20restaurant%20work%20not%20as%20a%20career%20but%20as%20an%20%26quot%3Bentry-level%20stepping%20stone%2C%26quot%3B%20Henkes%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20that%20reason%2C%20and%20because%20industry%20profit%20margins%20often%20hover%20around%20a%20scant%203%25%20to%205%25%2C%20it%20can%20be%20tough%20to%20persuade%20bosses%20to%20invest%20in%20workers%20who%20might%20not%20even%20last%20an%20entire%20%3Ca%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-chipotle-burrito-season-hiring-jobs-food-eating-out-2024-1%5C%22%3Eburrito%20season%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Yet%2C%20Henkes%20said%2C%20restaurants%20are%20increasingly%20putting%20money%20into%20hourly%20workers%20by%20offering%20%26quot%3Bcarrots%26quot%3B%20like%20partial%20college%20tuition%2C%20scholarships%2C%20and%20401(k)%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20measures%2C%20Henkes%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bshow%20that%20the%20restaurant%20is%20investing%20in%20the%20person.%26quot%3B%20That%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20can%20pay%20off%20by%20reducing%20the%20share%20of%20workers%20who%20hand%20in%20their%20aprons%20well%20before%20making%20it%20a%20year%20in%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Dash%20In%20cook%20prepares%20sandwiches.%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%2