e%20said.%20More%20than%2085%25%20of%20Chipotle%20managers%20started%20on%20store%20crews%2C%20Alexis-Collins%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20offers%20quarterly%20bonuses%20of%20a%20week's%20pay%20to%20crew%20members%20whose%20restaurants%20do%20well%2C%20up%20to%20%245%2C250%20a%20year%20for%20education%2C%20and%20a%20debt-free%20degree%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20most%20of%20its%20restaurant%20workers%20%26quot%3Bcome%20in%20wanting%20a%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlexis-Collins%20said%20Chipotle%20has%20tried%20to%20make%20improvements%2C%20especially%20at%20the%20general%20manager%20level%2C%20because%20they%20are%20%26quot%3Bthe%20captain%20of%20the%20ship.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20effort%20involves%20an%20artificial%20intelligence%20platform%20that%20chats%20with%20job%20candidates%2C%20collects%20their%20information%2C%20schedules%20interviews%2C%20and%20sends%20offer%20letters%20on%20a%20manager's%20behalf.%20Chipotle%20thinks%20the%20tool%2C%20called%20Ava%20Cado%2C%20could%20cut%20the%20time%20it%20takes%20to%20hire%20restaurant%20workers%20by%20as%20much%20as%2075%25.%20That's%20a%20help%20to%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20more%20stable%20the%20restaurant%20leader%20is%2C%20the%20better%20retention%20for%20the%20crew%20team%2C%26quot%3B%20Alexis-Collins%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChad%20Moutray%2C%20the%20National%20Restaurant%20Association's%20chief%20economist%2C%20likewise%20told%20BI%20that%20having%20the%20right%20manager%20in%20place%20matters%20not%20only%20for%20the%20bottom%20line%20but%20also%20for%20%26quot%3Bmaking%20sure%20that%20your%20workers%20are%20sticking%20around.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20a%20lot%20of%20food%20service%20workers%20tend%20to%20get%20jobs%20at%20places%20where%20they%20already%20eat.%20That%20creates%20a%20level%20of%20buy-in%20from%20the%20start%2C%20Moutray%20said.%20Yet%2C%20for%20employees%20to%20stay%2C%20they%20also%20need%20to%20feel%20appreciated%2C%20have%20colleagues%20they%20like%20working%20with%2C%20and%20have%20managers%20who%20lay%20out%20what's%20expected%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Dinner%20Party%20at%20Brooklyn.%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%227997%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6825fa8ec6ad288d1481056d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225334%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20right%20manager%20can%20make%20it%20easier%20for%20restaurant%20workers%20to%20stick%20with%20what%20can%20be%20a%20demanding%20job.%3Cp%3EAmy%20Lombard%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224ec3f2da-7f82-483f-ade6-803a183ef534%5C%22%3EGetting%20tech%20to%20do%20some%20gruntwork%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHenkes%2C%20from%20Technomic%2C%20said%20more%20restaurants%20are%20making%20%26quot%3Ba%20big%20push%26quot%3B%20to%20increase%20job%20satisfaction%20by%20using%20technology%20to%20take%20some%20menial%20tasks%20off%20workers'%20plates.%20That%20can%20include%20adding%20kiosks%20where%20customers%20place%20orders%20or%20introducing%20automation%20to%20the%20back-of-house%20areas%20where%20food%20gets%20prepped.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHenkes%20said%20that%20while%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20investments%20that%20restaurants%20are%20making%20in%20technology%20relate%20to%20labor%2C%20the%20goal%20generally%20isn't%20to%20replace%20workers.%20Instead%2C%20he%20said%2C%20it's%20to%20do%20things%20like%20automate%20taking%20inventory%20to%20free%20up%20workers%20to%20interact%20with%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20it's%20doing%20is%20redeploying%20them%20to%20higher-value%20activities%2C%26quot%3B%20Henkes%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20software%20that%20juggles%20workers'%20shift%20requests%20can%20give%20employees%20more%20predictability%20and%20flexibility%20in%20their%20schedules.%20That's%20important%20for%20boosting%20job%20satisfaction%2C%20but%20it%20also%20helps%20restaurant%20workers%20who%20hold%20down%20more%20than%20one%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20has%20become%20a%20very%20scientific%20approach%20to%20making%20sure%20that%20people%20are%20scheduled%20when%20they%20want%20to%20be%20and%20that%20shifts%20are%20covered%2C%26quot%3B%20Henkes%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228351f4b3-ac32-47bb-9be3-cbde775b97c7%5C%22%3EBoosting%20pay%20and%20benefits%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESchive%2C%20at%20Blue%20Loon%20Bakery%2C%20said%20that%20while%20labor%20is%20the%20cost%20that%20she%20has%20the%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emost%20control%20over%2C%20corralling%20employees%20is%20the%20hardest%20thing%20about%20running%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20recruit%20them%2C%20you%20train%20them%2C%20and%20then%20you%20have%20to%20retain%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchive%20uses%20a%20%3Ca%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flivingwage.mit.edu%2F%5C%22%3Ecalculator%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Massachusetts%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20to%20determine%20a%20%3Ca%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-should-invest-in-workers-and-pay-a-livable-wage-2022-5%5C%22%3Eliving%20wage%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20full-time%20workers%20at%20her%20New%20London%2C%20New%20Hampshire%2C%20bakery%2C%20which%20occupies%20a%20white%20clapboard%20house%20built%20in%20the%201830s%20and%20an%20attached%20barn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Blue%20Loon%20Bakery%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221576%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6824bae4c6ad288d1480e8b0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221046%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBlue%20Loon%20Bakery%20in%20New%20London%2C%20New%20Hampshire%2C%20has%20introduced%20a%20range%20of%20benefits%20to%20attract%20and%20retain%20workers.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Ethos%20%26amp%3B%20Able%20Creative%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20pandemic%20began%20to%20sub